    from {
      -webkit-transform: translate(0, 0);
    }
    to {
      -webkit-transform: translate(-300px, 0);
    }
  }

  .resultMarquee{
    -webkit-animation: scroll 7s linear 0 infinite;
    position: absolute;
  }</code></pre>

Integer overflow can be a causal cause of buffer overflow. Like this for example:<p><pre><code>  read(fd, &header, sizeof(header));
  int total_len = header.data_len + header.code_len;
  char *data = malloc(total_len);
  read(fd, data, total_len);
</code></pre>
Now, the attacker crafts the file and.. there&#x27;s your buffer overflow which is a <i>direct consequence</i> of undetected integer overflow [i.e., the program being allowed to proceed].
